9:
Too quiet. This place should be
teeming with other adventurers. We
weren't the only ones to take on this
request.
15: So the creature is a dragon?
19:
Well, technically it's a dragon-LIKE
creature. Nobody's sure what it
actually is.
22:
There's not much reliable
information, unfortunately. However,
given the incidents we've had
before, we feel it's best to act quickly.
27:
So basically we have no clue what
we're goin' into. Don't you think you
give us too many of these types of
jobs?
31:
That might be true! But... I have a
bad feeling about this one in
particular.
34:
The more help we can get the
better. We've even got fresh
adventurers working on this! Having
your support would really put my
mind at ease.
38:
If that's the case, I suppose it can't
be helped.
46:
This kind of reminds me of the time
we met Schult.
49:
So you think we've got another
ancient dragon on our hands?
54:
The legendary dragons of old are
not ones to make such casual
appearances.
59: Schult had a very big lunch today.
64:
He's graduated from just describing
flavors to actually having his own
tastes and preferences.
68:
Next thing you know you'll have him
talkin' like a normal person.
75:
Holy crap, that thing's huge. It's
almost as massive as Schult!
84: No doubt about it—that's a dragon!
87:
This sensation... It feels oddly
familiar...
92:
Alk and I will charge in first!
The rest of you help out all the
injured!
94:
Wait! You mustn't attack from the
front!
109:
Fall back.
This duty is mine alone.
126:
Thank you, Schult! If you hadn't
arrived, who knows what would
have happened.
130:
I am glad I wasn't too late.
I am... relieved.
133:
But why did you come here? Were
you aware of this other dragon's
presence?
137: The truth is... I don't know.
143:
Had I known it would come to this, I
would not have shunned contact
with other dragons for so long...
146:
I am sorry. This all happened
because I was such a shut-in...
151:
It's okay, Schult! You've adjusted so
well to the outside world already!
154:
There is one thing that I know for
certain: that creature is my enemy.
The very blood in my veins
proclaims it so.
156:
A voice rang out inside me, telling
me to stop it.
159:
This is perhaps my fate... The Law of
Ancients.
164:
Was coming to help us also a part
of your fate?
168:
No.
That I did entirely of my own will.
173:
Lucia... I thought I instructed you to
not to follow me. Your unshakable
determination confounds me.
180: Or perhaps I take after her.
183:
Let us depart.
I should wish to taste your cooking
once again!
187:
All right!
I hope you're in the mood for
something spicy!
191:
Light.
I have chosen... to fight against my
fate.
194:
What of you?
No, there is no need to even ask.
199:
Can I...
Go against my fate?
